The '''Jedi Schism''' was an event that split the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] three months after the start of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. Hundreds of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] refused the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council's]] orders for them to follow [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine's]] appointment of them to positions within the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]]. Their reasons included the belief that it was not a Jedi's position to lead armies, that the [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|Separatist Crisis]] should be handled through diplomacy and not war, and that they had better things to do.

At first, [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Sora Bulq/Legends|Sora Bulq]] was organized as their loose leader, but he was later [[Mission to Ruul (Clone Wars)|revealed]] to be working for the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]]. After that event, many of the Jedi returned to Republic service eventually, but others remained apart, exercising the [[Right of Denial]]. The Jedi Council allowed them to remain unmolested as long as they did not serve the CIS or fall to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]], but required many to hand in their [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]].

